# AutoClust - Harita Hive AI Clustering Tool
# MIT License
#
# AI-based clustering of spatial points
# Automatically determines optimal cluster count
#
# Features:
# - Multiple clustering algorithms (DBSCAN, K-means++, HDBSCAN)
# - Automatic optimal cluster count detection
# - Spatial constraints and barriers support
# - Outlier detection and handling
# - Cluster validation metrics
# - Interactive visualization
#
# Use Cases:
# - Crime hotspot analysis
# - Retail location optimization
# - Utility infrastructure planning
# - Disease outbreak clustering
# - Customer segmentation
#
# Algorithms:
# - DBSCAN: Density-based clustering
# - HDBSCAN: Hierarchical density clustering
# - K-means++: Improved centroid initialization
# - Spatial K-means: Geography-aware clustering
#
# Cluster Validation:
# - Silhouette score
# - Calinski-Harabasz index
# - Davies-Bouldin index
# - Spatial autocorrelation metrics
#
# Usage:
# autoclust --input points.shp --algorithm dbscan --auto-optimize
# autoclust --crime-data incidents.csv --temporal-clustering --export-report